    {
      "id": "1914750c-f3ba-8042-8d23-e5f5af1d3b74",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Peer assessment is a popular form of assessing learner ability but becomes more and more unmanageable as the number of students increases. This work uses item-response theory to improve the peer assessment step. Results show that approach is not significantly better than a random group formation.  ",
